FR940118-1-00053 FR940118-1-00008 ␣ 1New section 1Old section 1Section title 160.077&hyph;1 same Scope. 160.077&hyph;2 160.077&hyph;3 Definitions. 160.077&hyph;3 160.077&hyph;5 Required to be worn. 160.077&hyph;4 160.077&hyph;7 Type. 160.077&hyph;5 160.077&hyph;9 Incorporation by Reference. 160.077&hyph;6 160.077&hyph;33 Approval Procedures. 160.077&hyph;7 160.077&hyph;35 Procedure for Approval of Design or Material Revision. 160.077&hyph;9 160.077&hyph;37 Independent Laboratories. Remaining sections are unchanged. Changes to 46 CFR Subpart 25.25 Life Preservers and Other Lifesaving Equipment. Section 25.25&hyph;5␣Life Preservers and Other Lifesaving Equipment Required (f)(1) The text previously published as §25.25&hyph;5(f)(2) has been moved to this paragraph to make it clear only Type V commercial hybrid PFD's will be required to be worn as stated in the revised §25.25&hyph;5(f)(3). (f)(2) The text previously published as §25.25&hyph;5(f)(3) has been moved to this paragraph to make it clear only Type V commercial hybrid PFD's will be required to be worn as stated in the revised §25.25&hyph;5(f)(3). (f)(3) The Coast Guard proposes to revise the Scope in 46 CFR subpart 160.077&hyph;1(b) to indicate that hybrid PFD's approved as Type I devices do not have the restriction REQUIRED TO BE WORN. In keeping with the changes to the scope in 46 CFR subpart 160.077&hyph;1(b), the text (originally published as §25.25&hyph;5(f)(1)) will be moved to paragraph (f)(3) and will be changed to show that Type I commercial hybrid PFD's do not have to be worn to meet carriage requirements. Type V commercial hybrid PFD's remain ``Required To Be Worn.'' Changes To Make Editorial Corrections Section 160.077&hyph;3␣Definition. (a) This paragraph is revised to keep the definition of ``Commandant'' consistent with the definition found in Subpart 160.176&hyph;3. (h) This paragraph is revised to drop the reference to §175.3(b) as a result of the proposed rule changes to 33 CFR part 175 published in the Federal Register on November 9, 1992 (57 FR 53410). Section 160.077&hyph;11␣Flotation Material (b)(1)(iii) The Omnibus Trade and Competitiveness Act of 1988 amended the Metric Conversion Act of 1975 to declare that each federal agency shall change over to the metric system. This paragraph is revised in accordance with the Omnibus Trade and Competitiveness Act of 1988 to include metric as well as English measurements. Section 160.077&hyph;11␣Flotation Material (j) This paragraph is revised to change the subparagraph designation from an upper case (J) to a lower case (j). Section 160.077&hyph;15␣Construction and Performance_Recreational Hybrid PFD's (b)(15) Section 160.077&hyph;15(b)(13) is renumbered §160.077&hyph;15(b)(15) to incorporate the additional requirements proposed as §160.077&hyph;15(b) (13) and (14) in this SNPRM. Section 160.077&hyph;19␣Approval Testing_Recreational Hybrid PFD (e) This paragraph is revised to delete the text ``(G&hyph;MVI&hyph;3)'' in response to the change in definition of ``Commandant,'' discussed in §160.077&hyph;3(a) above. Section 160.077&hyph;21␣Approval Testing_Commercial Hybrid PFD (g) This paragraph is revised to delete the text ``(G&hyph;MVI&hyph;3)'' in response to the change in definition of ``Commandant,'' discussed in §160.077&hyph;3(a) above. Section 160.077&hyph;23␣General (a)(2) This paragraph is revised to delete the text ``(G&hyph;MVI&hyph;3)'' in response to the change in definition of ``Commandant,'' discussed in §160.077&hyph;3(a) above. Section 160.077&hyph;23␣Equipment (g)(3)(iii) This paragraph is revised to show that 14 g equals 0.5 oz. Section 160.077&hyph;23␣Independent Laboratory Inspection (j)(4)(iii) This paragraph is revised to delete the text ``(G&hyph;MVI&hyph;3)'' in response to the change in definition of ``Commandant,'' discussed in §160.077&hyph;3(a) above.
